Problem: Write a SELECT query to list students with the courses they are enrolled in, including the course name and grade. Return student_name, course_name, and grade. Order by student_name, then course_name.
Language: sql
Fix this failing code:
```sql
Here is the SQL query to list students with the courses they are enrolled in, including the course name and grade.
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (1, 'Alice Johnson', 'Computer Science', 2024);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (2, 'Bob Smith', 'Mathematics', 2023);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (3, 'Carol White', 'Computer Science', 2024);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (4, 'Dave Brown', 'Physics', 2022);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (5, 'Eve Davis', 'Mathematics', 2023);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (6, 'Frank Wilson', 'Computer Science', 2022);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (7, 'Grace Lee', 'Physics', 2024);
INSERT INTO students (id, name, major, year) VALUES (8, 'Henry Clark', 'Mathematics', 2022);

SELECT s.name AS student_name, c.name AS course_name, e.grade
FROM students s
JOIN enrollments e ON s.id = e.student_id
JOIN courses c ON e.course_id = c.id
ORDER BY s.name, c.name;
```
